            <title>[SPARK-38631] Arbitrary shell command injection via Utils.unpack()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-38631</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a risk for arbitrary shell command injection via &lt;tt&gt;Utils.unpack&lt;/tt&gt; when the filename is controlled by a malicious user. This is due to an issue in Hadoop&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;unTar&lt;/tt&gt;, that is not properly escaping the filename before passing to a shell command:&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop/blob/trunk/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/fs/FileUtil.java#L904&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hadoop/blob/trunk/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/fs/FileUtil.java#L904&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
